You have working code in your header, so you could probably more easily adapt that to send a specific option. The problem with a `button_to` is preparing the form-data (which a form does automatically obviously). But of course that is possible. So two options: 

### Use a fixed form 

    &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;col-md-6&quot;&gt;
        &lt;table class=&quot;table table-striped&quot;&gt;    
        &lt;% @playgrounds.each do |playground| %&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td class=&quot;col_narrow&quot;&gt; &lt;%= image_tag playground.logo if playground.logo.attached? %&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td class=&quot;col_narrow&quot;&gt; &lt;%= link_to playground.hierarchy, playground %&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td class=&quot;col_narrow&quot;&gt; 
              &lt;%= playground.translated_name %&gt;
              &lt;%= form_for(current_user, url: set_playground_user_path(current_user), method: :patch) do |f| %&gt;
                &lt;%= f.hidden_field :current_playground_id, value: playground.id %&gt;  
                &lt;%= f.submit &quot;Select&quot; %&gt;
              &lt;% end %&gt; 
            &lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td class=&quot;col_wide&quot;&gt; &lt;pre&gt; &lt;%= playground.translated_description %&gt; &lt;/pre&gt; &lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;% end %&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

### Build the form-data inside the button-to 

If you want to use the button-to, you need to send the correct data along: 

    &lt;%= button_to &#39;Select&#39;, [:set_playground, current_user], method: :patch, params: {user: { current_playground_id: playground.id }}) %&gt; 


(please note that `[:set_playground, current_user]` is identical to `set_playground_user_path(current_user)` so you can switch those if you want) 

